2 unit(s) Organic Chicken Breast
2 unit(s) Sweet Potato
0.17 cup Panko Breadcrumbs
4 tbsp Ranch Dressing
56 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
½ tbsp White Wine Vinegar
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
½ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Butter*
2.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
¼ tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Lightly oil the grill. While you prep, preheat the grill to medium-high (approx. 500°F).
Wash and dry all produce.
Peel, then cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch rounds.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets.) Season with salt, pepper and half the Zesty Garlic Blend. Toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 18-24 min, flipping halfway, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, switching baking sheet positions halfway through.)

Meanwhile, heat a medium non-stick pan over medium.
While the pan heats, halve cucumber lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
In a small bowl, combine ranch and half the Parmesan.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then half the panko (use all for 4 servings). Toast for 3-5 min, stirring often, until golden. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to a plate.

In a large bowl, whisk together half the vinegar (use all for 4 servings), half the mustard, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. (NOTE: This is your salad dressing.)
In another small bowl, combine mayo and remaining mustard. Season with salt and pepper. (NOTE: This is your dipping sauce.)

Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt, pepper and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend. Drizzle 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil over top. Flip to coat.
On a platter, gather chicken, a clean plate, Parmesan-ranch mixture, a spoon and any grilling tools, then head out to grill!

Add chicken to the grill. Reduce heat to medium, close lid and grill for 5-8 min per side until chicken is cooked through.**
When the chicken is done, spoon Parmesan-ranch mixture on top, close lid and grill for 2-4 min, until Parmesan melts.
Lightly press crumb topping on the tops of chicken, then let rest for 3 min.

To the bowl with salad dressing (from step 3), add spring mix and cucumbers, then toss to coat.
Divide chicken, potato coins and salad between plates.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over salad.
Serve mayo-mustard sauce alongside for dipping.